WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.010 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.010 --> 00:00:07.510 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY DYER: Is there a deeper,
hidden, more esoteric meaning

00:00:07.510 --> 00:00:09.820 align:middle line:84%
behind the Hollywood films
that we all love to watch?

00:00:09.820 --> 00:00:10.810 align:middle line:90%
I'm Jay Dyer.

00:00:10.810 --> 00:00:11.690 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY WEIDNER: And
I'm Jay Weidner.

00:00:11.690 --> 00:00:13.301 align:middle line:90%
And this is "Hollywood Decoded."

00:00:13.301 --> 00:00:16.247 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:16.247 --> 00:00:23.140 align:middle line:90%


00:00:23.140 --> 00:00:25.660 align:middle line:84%
So we chose these two
movies, "The Last Mimzy"

00:00:25.660 --> 00:00:28.450 align:middle line:84%
and "9," because
they both came out

00:00:28.450 --> 00:00:30.040 align:middle line:90%
around the same time period.

00:00:30.040 --> 00:00:32.350 align:middle line:10%
They're both ostensibly
children's films--

00:00:32.350 --> 00:00:34.210 align:middle line:10%
although I don't
think they really are.

00:00:34.210 --> 00:00:37.420 align:middle line:10%
And finally, they have
very similar plots.

00:00:37.420 --> 00:00:40.120 align:middle line:84%
In "The Last Mimzy,"
the scientist

00:00:40.120 --> 00:00:44.270 align:middle line:84%
sends an object into the past
to save his world, his dystopian

00:00:44.270 --> 00:00:45.070 align:middle line:90%
world.

00:00:45.070 --> 00:00:48.610 align:middle line:84%
And in "9," the scientist
sends something into the future

00:00:48.610 --> 00:00:50.440 align:middle line:90%
to save his dystopian world.

00:00:50.440 --> 00:00:53.900 align:middle line:84%
Again, both movies are
very similar, but one,

00:00:53.900 --> 00:00:56.610 align:middle line:84%
I think "9" is a little more
deeper than "The Last Mimzy,"

00:00:56.610 --> 00:00:58.960 align:middle line:84%
but I think "The Last Mimzy"
still is important enough

00:00:58.960 --> 00:01:01.756 align:middle line:84%
for us to make at least
a brief comment on it.

00:01:01.756 --> 00:01:03.130 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: Yeah, I
think that you're

00:01:03.130 --> 00:01:04.463 align:middle line:90%
right that they're very similar.

00:01:04.463 --> 00:01:07.510 align:middle line:84%
They both have the same
patterns, the same themes.

00:01:07.510 --> 00:01:14.620 align:middle line:84%
They're looking at reality
from a Platonic, Pythagorean

00:01:14.620 --> 00:01:17.560 align:middle line:90%
and almost, at times, Gnostic.

00:01:17.560 --> 00:01:19.450 align:middle line:84%
Especially with
"9," we get the idea

00:01:19.450 --> 00:01:24.370 align:middle line:84%
of the original creator being,
again, this one, this monad,

00:01:24.370 --> 00:01:26.080 align:middle line:90%
this unifying source.

00:01:26.080 --> 00:01:28.150 align:middle line:84%
In this case, it's a
human being who creates,

00:01:28.150 --> 00:01:32.050 align:middle line:84%
and then these entities
that are mechanical

00:01:32.050 --> 00:01:33.970 align:middle line:90%
are lacking their soul.

00:01:33.970 --> 00:01:35.860 align:middle line:84%
In contrast, in
"The Last Mimzy,"

00:01:35.860 --> 00:01:39.550 align:middle line:84%
you have human beings
that are warned

00:01:39.550 --> 00:01:43.007 align:middle line:84%
about an ecological
disaster in the near future.

00:01:43.007 --> 00:01:44.590 align:middle line:84%
And so what they
have to do is, again,

00:01:44.590 --> 00:01:49.732 align:middle line:84%
find their soul to avoid a
toxic and transhumanist future.

00:01:49.732 --> 00:01:51.690 align:middle line:84%
If you noticed, at the
end of "The Last Mimzy,"

00:01:51.690 --> 00:01:55.030 align:middle line:84%
everybody's having to wear
these exoskeleton suits

00:01:55.030 --> 00:01:58.340 align:middle line:84%
that protect them from a toxic
environment due to contaminated

00:01:58.340 --> 00:01:59.140 align:middle line:90%
DNA.

00:01:59.140 --> 00:02:04.420 align:middle line:84%
So both stories are
apocalyptic, basically.

00:02:04.420 --> 00:02:06.730 align:middle line:84%
But they also present
hope and, again,

00:02:06.730 --> 00:02:09.970 align:middle line:84%
the avoidance of the
apocalypse through, again,

00:02:09.970 --> 00:02:11.560 align:middle line:90%
operating in wisdom.

00:02:11.560 --> 00:02:14.770 align:middle line:84%
We are so focused on
knowledge in our era,

00:02:14.770 --> 00:02:17.230 align:middle line:84%
and collecting facts
and data, but it really

00:02:17.230 --> 00:02:20.140 align:middle line:84%
doesn't aid us unless
we are wise in the way

00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:21.691 align:middle line:90%
that we use this data.

00:02:21.691 --> 00:02:22.690 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: That's right.

00:02:22.690 --> 00:02:25.930 align:middle line:84%
Wisdom is taking knowledge
and then combining it

00:02:25.930 --> 00:02:26.900 align:middle line:90%
into a newer form.

00:02:26.900 --> 00:02:27.700 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Right.

00:02:27.700 --> 00:02:30.380 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: And I think that
there's both Buddhist concepts,

00:02:30.380 --> 00:02:33.520 align:middle line:84%
Gnostic concepts,
Pythagorean concepts,

00:02:33.520 --> 00:02:37.600 align:middle line:84%
sacred geometry concepts,
and this kind of--

00:02:37.600 --> 00:02:39.580 align:middle line:84%
like the grandfather
paradox of time,

00:02:39.580 --> 00:02:43.177 align:middle line:84%
having to go back to get DNA
to save the future, which

00:02:43.177 --> 00:02:44.260 align:middle line:90%
is what the movie's about.

00:02:44.260 --> 00:02:44.950 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Right, right.

00:02:44.950 --> 00:02:46.330 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: So
these two kids find

00:02:46.330 --> 00:02:50.440 align:middle line:84%
this rabbit on the beach up
in the Pacific Northwest.

00:02:50.440 --> 00:02:56.320 align:middle line:84%
And this rabbit, we later
discover, has deep circuitry.

00:02:56.320 --> 00:02:58.781 align:middle line:90%
It's an AI, it's a form of AI.

00:02:58.781 --> 00:03:00.280 align:middle line:84%
And these kids
discover it, and they

00:03:00.280 --> 00:03:04.570 align:middle line:84%
begin getting superpowers from
this stuffed rabbit, which

00:03:04.570 --> 00:03:05.950 align:middle line:90%
is Mimzy.

00:03:05.950 --> 00:03:10.870 align:middle line:84%
And the boy, Noah,
and the girl, Emma,

00:03:10.870 --> 00:03:14.530 align:middle line:84%
who are brother
and sister, begin

00:03:14.530 --> 00:03:16.480 align:middle line:90%
taking on these superpowers.

00:03:16.480 --> 00:03:20.470 align:middle line:84%
And also, Noah begins
drawing Sri Yantras

00:03:20.470 --> 00:03:22.870 align:middle line:84%
and other sacred
geometrical forms,

00:03:22.870 --> 00:03:25.189 align:middle line:84%
and he really doesn't
understand what he's doing

00:03:25.189 --> 00:03:26.980 align:middle line:84%
or where it's coming
from, but it's clearly

00:03:26.980 --> 00:03:30.610 align:middle line:84%
coming from the last
Mimzy, this stuffed rabbit.

00:03:30.610 --> 00:03:35.800 align:middle line:84%
And eventually, he
becomes a genius because

00:03:35.800 --> 00:03:37.480 align:middle line:90%
of his interactions with it.

00:03:37.480 --> 00:03:40.420 align:middle line:84%
And then he designs
the machine that

00:03:40.420 --> 00:03:43.910 align:middle line:84%
will send the DNA
into the future, which

00:03:43.910 --> 00:03:48.160 align:middle line:84%
was the whole point of the
experiment throughout the film.

00:03:48.160 --> 00:03:51.970 align:middle line:84%
The scientist who made
the last Mimzy wanted

00:03:51.970 --> 00:03:55.040 align:middle line:84%
some pure, innocent
people to find it--

00:03:55.040 --> 00:03:55.840 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Right.

00:03:55.840 --> 00:03:58.060 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: --capture
that DNA, and then

00:03:58.060 --> 00:03:59.870 align:middle line:90%
send it into the future.

00:03:59.870 --> 00:04:02.510 align:middle line:10%
>>DYER: Yeah, it's based
on the Adam and Eve myth.

00:04:02.510 --> 00:04:04.930 align:middle line:10%
And so you've got
Adam and Eve, and then

00:04:04.930 --> 00:04:07.180 align:middle line:10%
regular humanity that
expand from them.

00:04:07.180 --> 00:04:09.040 align:middle line:84%
And then we need a new
Adam and a new Eve.

00:04:09.040 --> 00:04:11.220 align:middle line:84%
And so the two,
brother and sister,

00:04:11.220 --> 00:04:13.420 align:middle line:84%
are actually going to
function in that capacity.

00:04:13.420 --> 00:04:16.930 align:middle line:84%
Noah's going to be, in a
way, like Noah from Genesis

00:04:16.930 --> 00:04:18.930 align:middle line:90%
8, the Noah's ark story.

00:04:18.930 --> 00:04:20.560 align:middle line:90%
He's going to be the engineer.

00:04:20.560 --> 00:04:24.440 align:middle line:84%
He's going to help his sister,
who is the feminine archetype.

00:04:24.440 --> 00:04:25.450 align:middle line:90%
She's more intuitive.

00:04:25.450 --> 00:04:29.500 align:middle line:84%
She has these separate
powers from him.

00:04:29.500 --> 00:04:32.020 align:middle line:84%
He has certain powers,
like telekinesis,

00:04:32.020 --> 00:04:33.910 align:middle line:90%
and he can open these portals.

00:04:33.910 --> 00:04:35.590 align:middle line:10%
And what's interesting
is that it's

00:04:35.590 --> 00:04:38.450 align:middle line:10%
done through the
idea of the yantra,

00:04:38.450 --> 00:04:40.600 align:middle line:10%
an Ancient Indian philosophy.

00:04:40.600 --> 00:04:44.080 align:middle line:84%
This is the idea that certain
forms, geometrical forms,

00:04:44.080 --> 00:04:46.150 align:middle line:84%
can actually tap
into other planes.

00:04:46.150 --> 00:04:48.730 align:middle line:84%
And it also connects to
vibrations and sounds,

00:04:48.730 --> 00:04:51.910 align:middle line:84%
which is why he has the ability
to speak to bugs and insects,

00:04:51.910 --> 00:04:53.080 align:middle line:90%
and move them around.

00:04:53.080 --> 00:04:56.300 align:middle line:84%
And it's all done
through vocal intonation.

00:04:56.300 --> 00:05:01.480 align:middle line:84%
So what Noah does is tap
into higher frequencies.

00:05:01.480 --> 00:05:04.540 align:middle line:84%
And I believe that it is true
that these different levels

00:05:04.540 --> 00:05:06.610 align:middle line:84%
of reality that we
experience, they

00:05:06.610 --> 00:05:09.690 align:middle line:84%
do happen at different
vibrations or frequencies.

00:05:09.690 --> 00:05:11.650 align:middle line:84%
And so that aspect
of the movie I

00:05:11.650 --> 00:05:13.380 align:middle line:84%
found interesting,
very fascinating.

00:05:13.380 --> 00:05:14.180 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Me too.

00:05:14.180 --> 00:05:17.530 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: So what's going
on here is the pooling

00:05:17.530 --> 00:05:21.520 align:middle line:84%
of both the rational, and
scientific, analytical left

00:05:21.520 --> 00:05:24.930 align:middle line:84%
brain in the character of
Noah in his engineering.

00:05:24.930 --> 00:05:26.470 align:middle line:84%
And then we have
the more intuitive,

00:05:26.470 --> 00:05:29.490 align:middle line:84%
the right brain, the
creativity on the part of Emma.

00:05:29.490 --> 00:05:31.560 align:middle line:84%
And so she's functioning
like a new Eve,

00:05:31.560 --> 00:05:32.820 align:middle line:90%
a new mother of humanity.

00:05:32.820 --> 00:05:35.278 align:middle line:84%
That's what her role is going
to be at the end of the film.

00:05:35.278 --> 00:05:39.310 align:middle line:84%
She's described as the new Eve,
the new mother of the world.

00:05:39.310 --> 00:05:41.340 align:middle line:90%
He's the new Adam, in a way.

00:05:41.340 --> 00:05:43.930 align:middle line:84%
So I like that we have this
balance between the right brain

00:05:43.930 --> 00:05:47.220 align:middle line:84%
and the left brain, between
analytical and intuitive,

00:05:47.220 --> 00:05:48.090 align:middle line:90%
creative thinking.

00:05:48.090 --> 00:05:51.220 align:middle line:84%
And that's the most positive
aspect to this film, I think,

00:05:51.220 --> 00:05:55.320 align:middle line:84%
is that when they're
faced with the raid

00:05:55.320 --> 00:05:57.930 align:middle line:84%
by Homeland Security,
and these different FBI

00:05:57.930 --> 00:06:01.080 align:middle line:84%
agents, and whatnot,
they don't understand

00:06:01.080 --> 00:06:03.630 align:middle line:84%
that there are people that are
gifted, there are people that

00:06:03.630 --> 00:06:06.330 align:middle line:84%
are geniuses, indigo
children, that

00:06:06.330 --> 00:06:09.930 align:middle line:84%
are way ahead of
this sort of base,

00:06:09.930 --> 00:06:13.470 align:middle line:84%
or governmental
control type thinking.

00:06:13.470 --> 00:06:15.300 align:middle line:84%
And I like that
aspect of the film,

00:06:15.300 --> 00:06:17.649 align:middle line:84%
that they're actually
giving credence to--

00:06:17.649 --> 00:06:19.440 align:middle line:84%
the only way that we're
going to move ahead

00:06:19.440 --> 00:06:23.100 align:middle line:84%
in the world, progress
truly, is by listening

00:06:23.100 --> 00:06:24.630 align:middle line:84%
to these spiritually
gifted people.

00:06:24.630 --> 00:06:26.130 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: These
archetypes are also

00:06:26.130 --> 00:06:30.360 align:middle line:84%
reflected in the teacher
and his girlfriend, who

00:06:30.360 --> 00:06:32.310 align:middle line:90%
discover Emma and Noah.

00:06:32.310 --> 00:06:33.630 align:middle line:90%
He's a science teacher.

00:06:33.630 --> 00:06:34.740 align:middle line:90%
He's a rational.

00:06:34.740 --> 00:06:35.700 align:middle line:90%
She's a Buddhist.

00:06:35.700 --> 00:06:36.600 align:middle line:90%
She meditates.

00:06:36.600 --> 00:06:37.950 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Good point.

00:06:37.950 --> 00:06:40.350 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Yeah, and
she understands it

00:06:40.350 --> 00:06:44.100 align:middle line:84%
before he understands it,
because she understands the Sri

00:06:44.100 --> 00:06:45.900 align:middle line:90%
Yantra and what it really means.

00:06:45.900 --> 00:06:48.750 align:middle line:84%
And he just is familiar
with the imagery.

00:06:48.750 --> 00:06:52.700 align:middle line:84%
He's not familiar with the
intrinsic symbology of the Sri

00:06:52.700 --> 00:06:54.220 align:middle line:90%
Yantra, but she is.

00:06:54.220 --> 00:06:56.910 align:middle line:84%
And then they go to try
to tell their parents

00:06:56.910 --> 00:06:58.110 align:middle line:90%
about their gifted kids.

00:06:58.110 --> 00:06:59.790 align:middle line:84%
And of course, the
parents rejected them

00:06:59.790 --> 00:07:00.660 align:middle line:90%
and say it's not true.

00:07:00.660 --> 00:07:02.070 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: As an example
of that, let's look

00:07:02.070 --> 00:07:03.970 align:middle line:84%
at the clip, "How did
you do that, Noah?"

00:07:03.970 --> 00:07:05.416 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:07:05.416 --> 00:07:08.308 align:middle line:90%
[WHIRRING]

00:07:08.308 --> 00:07:17.000 align:middle line:90%


00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:21.310 align:middle line:10%
We have this idea in
ancient Platonism--

00:07:21.310 --> 00:07:23.980 align:middle line:10%
the fundamental fabric
and structure of reality

00:07:23.980 --> 00:07:26.470 align:middle line:10%
is actually psyche
or ideal forms.

00:07:26.470 --> 00:07:28.570 align:middle line:90%
And so it does have a pattern.

00:07:28.570 --> 00:07:30.040 align:middle line:90%
It does have a structure.

00:07:30.040 --> 00:07:31.600 align:middle line:84%
And what you're
seeing in this image

00:07:31.600 --> 00:07:34.915 align:middle line:84%
is the interconnectedness of
all these forms, these objects.

00:07:34.915 --> 00:07:36.790 align:middle line:84%
They appear to be
separate, but they actually

00:07:36.790 --> 00:07:38.748 align:middle line:84%
have an underlying
structure that unifies them.

00:07:38.748 --> 00:07:42.820 align:middle line:84%
And so what's happening is that
he's tapping into that unity.

00:07:42.820 --> 00:07:46.090 align:middle line:84%
And he's able to, by
thought, move this object

00:07:46.090 --> 00:07:47.020 align:middle line:90%
to another location.

00:07:47.020 --> 00:07:49.159 align:middle line:84%
And so really, time and
space are, in the film,

00:07:49.159 --> 00:07:50.450 align:middle line:90%
presented as somewhat relative.

00:07:50.450 --> 00:07:56.895 align:middle line:84%
They're really relative to our
perception of those relations.

00:07:56.895 --> 00:07:57.877 align:middle line:90%
[BOOM]

00:07:57.877 --> 00:07:58.859 align:middle line:90%
[GASP]

00:07:58.859 --> 00:07:59.659 align:middle line:90%
- Huh.

00:07:59.659 --> 00:08:00.823 align:middle line:90%
[GIGGLE]

00:08:00.823 --> 00:08:01.805 align:middle line:90%


00:08:01.805 --> 00:08:03.207 align:middle line:90%
What did I just do?

00:08:03.207 --> 00:08:04.290 align:middle line:90%
- How'd you do that, Noah?

00:08:04.290 --> 00:08:05.170 align:middle line:90%
- I don't know.

00:08:05.170 --> 00:08:06.130 align:middle line:90%
With my brain?

00:08:06.130 --> 00:08:09.706 align:middle line:84%
I just looked at it,
and it disappeared.

00:08:09.706 --> 00:08:10.506 align:middle line:90%
[WHOOSH]

00:08:10.506 --> 00:08:11.994 align:middle line:90%
[SQUEAL]

00:08:11.994 --> 00:08:12.990 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:08:12.990 --> 00:08:14.690 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: So in Indian
philosophy, you

00:08:14.690 --> 00:08:17.240 align:middle line:84%
have this idea of
the yantra, which

00:08:17.240 --> 00:08:19.310 align:middle line:90%
is a spiritual technology.

00:08:19.310 --> 00:08:23.810 align:middle line:84%
It's revelatory of deeper
metaphysical truths,

00:08:23.810 --> 00:08:24.710 align:middle line:90%
you might say.

00:08:24.710 --> 00:08:29.522 align:middle line:84%
So what we have is that
there's a conceptual loom.

00:08:29.522 --> 00:08:31.730 align:middle line:84%
So when I'm talking about
the forms or the underlying

00:08:31.730 --> 00:08:33.470 align:middle line:84%
structure, there's
a relationship

00:08:33.470 --> 00:08:37.694 align:middle line:84%
between all objects, and
it's mapped out, in a way.

00:08:37.694 --> 00:08:40.110 align:middle line:84%
As we're going to see when we
talk about "9," for example,

00:08:40.110 --> 00:08:41.150 align:middle line:90%
the works of Paracelsus.

00:08:41.150 --> 00:08:42.919 align:middle line:10%
He talks about a matrix.

00:08:42.919 --> 00:08:44.510 align:middle line:10%
He's writing this
back in the 1500s.

00:08:44.510 --> 00:08:47.210 align:middle line:10%
And he says that all reality
is connected and birthed out

00:08:47.210 --> 00:08:49.680 align:middle line:10%
of this primal matrix.

00:08:49.680 --> 00:08:52.160 align:middle line:84%
So in the same way, I think
Ancient Indian philosophy had

00:08:52.160 --> 00:08:55.220 align:middle line:84%
some prototypical
notion of this,

00:08:55.220 --> 00:09:00.320 align:middle line:84%
that all objects can,
therefore, be accessed,

00:09:00.320 --> 00:09:05.210 align:middle line:84%
or their essence is tapped into,
by these different frequencies.

00:09:05.210 --> 00:09:06.920 align:middle line:84%
This is something that
Tesla tapped into.

00:09:06.920 --> 00:09:09.350 align:middle line:84%
This is how he figured out
that certain notes could

00:09:09.350 --> 00:09:10.430 align:middle line:90%
break glass.

00:09:10.430 --> 00:09:11.930 align:middle line:84%
So that that
frequency is actually

00:09:11.930 --> 00:09:15.487 align:middle line:84%
disrupting the molecules
in the structure of glass.

00:09:15.487 --> 00:09:17.570 align:middle line:84%
And I think that all of
these ideas are connected.

00:09:17.570 --> 00:09:19.880 align:middle line:84%
And it all goes
back to what we've

00:09:19.880 --> 00:09:22.460 align:middle line:84%
seen in ancient philosophy,
ancient religion,

00:09:22.460 --> 00:09:24.710 align:middle line:84%
the idea of everything
being connected

00:09:24.710 --> 00:09:26.160 align:middle line:90%
in this metaphysical sense.

00:09:26.160 --> 00:09:27.980 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Yeah, and
Noah uses sound--

00:09:27.980 --> 00:09:28.280 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Right.

00:09:28.280 --> 00:09:29.780 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: --to
manipulate matter.

00:09:29.780 --> 00:09:34.050 align:middle line:84%
And we know from the works
of Hans Jenny in cymatics

00:09:34.050 --> 00:09:37.550 align:middle line:84%
that we can make geometric
forms using frequencies.

00:09:37.550 --> 00:09:40.460 align:middle line:90%
[HIGH FREQUENCY NOTE PLAYING]

00:09:40.460 --> 00:09:44.340 align:middle line:90%


00:09:44.340 --> 00:09:46.765 align:middle line:90%
[HIGHER NOTE PLAYING]

00:09:46.765 --> 00:09:50.140 align:middle line:90%


00:09:50.140 --> 00:09:50.940 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Right.

00:09:50.940 --> 00:09:53.590 align:middle line:84%
And they learn the
sacred geometry in this

00:09:53.590 --> 00:09:56.080 align:middle line:84%
from their dream state,
which is interesting.

00:09:56.080 --> 00:09:57.510 align:middle line:84%
Like in Ancient
Indian philosophy,

00:09:57.510 --> 00:09:59.920 align:middle line:84%
the waking state is just as
important as the dream state.

00:09:59.920 --> 00:10:02.620 align:middle line:84%
So the outer world is what you
experience in the waking state.

00:10:02.620 --> 00:10:04.450 align:middle line:84%
The inner world is
the dream state.

00:10:04.450 --> 00:10:06.760 align:middle line:84%
And in both, what
connects the two,

00:10:06.760 --> 00:10:09.950 align:middle line:84%
according to Carl Jung and even
the physicist Wolfgang Pauli,

00:10:09.950 --> 00:10:10.990 align:middle line:90%
is archetypes.

00:10:10.990 --> 00:10:13.790 align:middle line:84%
Both of those worlds are
connected through archetypes.

00:10:13.790 --> 00:10:15.550 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Yeah,
and the archetype

00:10:15.550 --> 00:10:19.240 align:middle line:84%
for the rabbit, the last Mimzy
is, of course, the White Rabbit

00:10:19.240 --> 00:10:20.270 align:middle line:90%
in Alice in Wonderland.

00:10:20.270 --> 00:10:21.186 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Yeah, exactly.

00:10:21.186 --> 00:10:23.500 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: And there's a
direct connection to the film.

00:10:23.500 --> 00:10:24.370 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: Yeah, it's
referenced, right?

00:10:24.370 --> 00:10:25.470 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Yeah, so
let's watch that.

00:10:25.470 --> 00:10:26.270 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:10:26.270 --> 00:10:27.640 align:middle line:90%
- Why are you showing me that?

00:10:27.640 --> 00:10:31.557 align:middle line:84%
- It's about Alice going
through the looking glass.

00:10:31.557 --> 00:10:33.959 align:middle line:84%
I think it explains
what the machine is.

00:10:33.959 --> 00:10:38.450 align:middle line:90%


00:10:38.450 --> 00:10:41.450 align:middle line:90%
- Wait a minute.

00:10:41.450 --> 00:10:43.740 align:middle line:90%
That looks like Mimzy.

00:10:43.740 --> 00:10:45.250 align:middle line:90%
How could she have Mimzy?

00:10:45.250 --> 00:10:46.950 align:middle line:90%
That was a hundred years ago.

00:10:46.950 --> 00:10:50.160 align:middle line:84%
- Maybe she has
spinners too, Noah.

00:10:50.160 --> 00:10:53.490 align:middle line:84%
Maybe she didn't get what
she was supposed to do.

00:10:53.490 --> 00:10:55.670 align:middle line:84%
Maybe she needed a
brother like you.

00:10:55.670 --> 00:10:56.470 align:middle line:90%
- Like me?

00:10:56.470 --> 00:10:58.180 align:middle line:90%
What for?

00:10:58.180 --> 00:11:00.400 align:middle line:90%
- Because you're my engineer.

00:11:00.400 --> 00:11:01.865 align:middle line:84%
- What do you mean
your "engineer"?

00:11:01.865 --> 00:11:03.930 align:middle line:84%
- I mean I can't do
it all alone, Noah.

00:11:03.930 --> 00:11:07.635 align:middle line:90%


00:11:07.635 --> 00:11:10.110 align:middle line:90%
Noah, I have to look.

00:11:10.110 --> 00:11:49.215 align:middle line:90%


00:11:49.215 --> 00:11:50.105 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:11:50.105 --> 00:11:51.730 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: So we have
the direct reference

00:11:51.730 --> 00:11:53.470 align:middle line:84%
to "Alice and the
Looking Glass."

00:11:53.470 --> 00:11:54.270 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Yeah.

00:11:54.270 --> 00:11:56.100 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: And that
is oftentimes read

00:11:56.100 --> 00:11:58.990 align:middle line:84%
as something related to MKUltra,
but it's not necessarily

00:11:58.990 --> 00:11:59.790 align:middle line:90%
about that.

00:11:59.790 --> 00:12:01.510 align:middle line:84%
It is at times,
but in the context

00:12:01.510 --> 00:12:05.140 align:middle line:84%
here, it's about seeing into
other planes of existence,

00:12:05.140 --> 00:12:08.662 align:middle line:84%
other levels of reality,
other metaphysical dimensions.

00:12:08.662 --> 00:12:10.370 align:middle line:84%
And that's exactly
what's happening here.

00:12:10.370 --> 00:12:12.760 align:middle line:84%
She's considering
the possibility

00:12:12.760 --> 00:12:15.190 align:middle line:84%
that the world that
she's presented with

00:12:15.190 --> 00:12:17.950 align:middle line:84%
is not necessarily
the true reality.

00:12:17.950 --> 00:12:20.740 align:middle line:84%
And I love the contrast between
the children and their parents.

00:12:20.740 --> 00:12:23.030 align:middle line:84%
The parents are caught
up in the mundane.

00:12:23.030 --> 00:12:25.962 align:middle line:84%
They initially are very
hostile to the children.

00:12:25.962 --> 00:12:27.670 align:middle line:84%
They don't want anything
to do with this.

00:12:27.670 --> 00:12:29.544 align:middle line:84%
They want to stop their
children from looking

00:12:29.544 --> 00:12:31.597 align:middle line:84%
deeper into the rabbit
hole and so forth.

00:12:31.597 --> 00:12:33.430 align:middle line:84%
But she's willing to
do it with her brother.

00:12:33.430 --> 00:12:36.660 align:middle line:84%
They have the male and the
female principles united there.

00:12:36.660 --> 00:12:38.410 align:middle line:84%
And that's ultimately
what saves humanity,

00:12:38.410 --> 00:12:40.990 align:middle line:84%
is this union that we've
been talking about.

00:12:40.990 --> 00:12:44.050 align:middle line:84%
And I like, also, that the
film even explicitly mentions

00:12:44.050 --> 00:12:44.960 align:middle line:90%
Platonic solids.

00:12:44.960 --> 00:12:45.760 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Yeah.

00:12:45.760 --> 00:12:48.160 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: I took philosophy
classes in college,

00:12:48.160 --> 00:12:51.010 align:middle line:84%
and we did Plato, and we didn't
talk about Platonic solids.

00:12:51.010 --> 00:12:51.860 align:middle line:90%
Now why is that?

00:12:51.860 --> 00:12:54.700 align:middle line:84%
I think it's because
it suppresses the truth

00:12:54.700 --> 00:12:57.610 align:middle line:84%
that the world around
us is not dead matter,

00:12:57.610 --> 00:12:59.350 align:middle line:84%
it's actually built
up, as I've said,

00:12:59.350 --> 00:13:02.594 align:middle line:84%
of geometrical forms and
principles, which shows not

00:13:02.594 --> 00:13:04.510 align:middle line:84%
just the union of all
things, but that there's

00:13:04.510 --> 00:13:07.360 align:middle line:84%
some actual creative source
from which all things come.

00:13:07.360 --> 00:13:09.975 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: And that geometry
is the underlying matrix

00:13:09.975 --> 00:13:13.750 align:middle line:84%
of our reality, which is why
mathematics is so important.

00:13:13.750 --> 00:13:17.680 align:middle line:84%
Speaking of mathematics,
Mimzy, the rabbit,

00:13:17.680 --> 00:13:20.950 align:middle line:84%
has a [INAUDIBLE]
spiral on it, which

00:13:20.950 --> 00:13:25.180 align:middle line:84%
is the symbol of
transiting between worlds,

00:13:25.180 --> 00:13:28.570 align:middle line:84%
and how nature unfolds,
unpacks itself.

00:13:28.570 --> 00:13:30.235 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: Right, the
Fibonacci sequence.

00:13:30.235 --> 00:13:31.568 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: The Fibonacci series.

00:13:31.568 --> 00:13:34.420 align:middle line:84%
And we see it in
this next scene where

00:13:34.420 --> 00:13:38.500 align:middle line:84%
Emma gives the future
her DNA, and she becomes

00:13:38.500 --> 00:13:39.760 align:middle line:90%
the mother of the future.

00:13:39.760 --> 00:13:40.566 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:13:40.566 --> 00:13:43.280 align:middle line:90%
- I don't want Mimzy to die.

00:13:43.280 --> 00:13:45.730 align:middle line:90%
- Mimzy's not going to die.

00:13:45.730 --> 00:13:48.180 align:middle line:90%
[CRYING]

00:13:48.180 --> 00:13:52.120 align:middle line:90%


00:13:52.120 --> 00:13:55.440 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Emma has given
her DNA to the Mimzy,

00:13:55.440 --> 00:13:57.660 align:middle line:84%
and now the mission is
pretty much complete.

00:13:57.660 --> 00:14:00.180 align:middle line:84%
Now the Mimzy just has to
go back into the future,

00:14:00.180 --> 00:14:02.420 align:middle line:84%
and they can
reinvigorate the DNA.

00:14:02.420 --> 00:14:03.300 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:14:03.300 --> 00:14:06.060 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: Yeah, it's interesting
that the film functions

00:14:06.060 --> 00:14:08.760 align:middle line:84%
as a warning about
genetic modification.

00:14:08.760 --> 00:14:11.070 align:middle line:84%
That comes up more
than once in the film.

00:14:11.070 --> 00:14:15.810 align:middle line:84%
They talk about contaminating
the genetic code with GMO.

00:14:15.810 --> 00:14:16.710 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Mm-hmm.

00:14:16.710 --> 00:14:20.010 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: And so she functions
as this savior figure

00:14:20.010 --> 00:14:23.520 align:middle line:84%
by her tear going
into the future,

00:14:23.520 --> 00:14:29.460 align:middle line:84%
and, therefore, returning
some pure genetic lineage.

00:14:29.460 --> 00:14:32.040 align:middle line:84%
That's, I think, a
prescient warning.

00:14:32.040 --> 00:14:35.280 align:middle line:84%
I think that's one of the
ways that we can possibly

00:14:35.280 --> 00:14:39.690 align:middle line:84%
assess this film, that
genetic modification can

00:14:39.690 --> 00:14:41.440 align:middle line:90%
be a serious danger.

00:14:41.440 --> 00:14:44.940 align:middle line:84%
We don't know what the effects
of releasing GMO salmon

00:14:44.940 --> 00:14:46.450 align:middle line:90%
into the waters is going to be.

00:14:46.450 --> 00:14:47.100 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: No, we don't.

00:14:47.100 --> 00:14:48.340 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: We're actually
doing this stuff.

00:14:48.340 --> 00:14:49.560 align:middle line:84%
So I think we need
to pay attention

00:14:49.560 --> 00:14:50.730 align:middle line:90%
to these kinds of warnings.

00:14:50.730 --> 00:14:52.854 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Yeah, and there
is, of course, early on,

00:14:52.854 --> 00:14:55.500 align:middle line:84%
the scene where the science
professor is showing

00:14:55.500 --> 00:14:57.060 align:middle line:90%
the kids the two-headed snake.

00:14:57.060 --> 00:14:58.640 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Exactly.

00:14:58.640 --> 00:15:00.900 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: It's the hydra.

00:15:00.900 --> 00:15:04.380 align:middle line:84%
The hydra is this
mutant reptile.

00:15:04.380 --> 00:15:07.362 align:middle line:84%
And I think that was
very indicative of what

00:15:07.362 --> 00:15:08.820 align:middle line:84%
they're trying to
say in this movie

00:15:08.820 --> 00:15:11.000 align:middle line:90%
about genetic modification.

00:15:11.000 --> 00:15:17.090 align:middle line:84%
And the plot of the movie
is that the dystopian future

00:15:17.090 --> 00:15:19.930 align:middle line:84%
has been created by
genetic modification.

00:15:19.930 --> 00:15:20.730 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Exactly.

00:15:20.730 --> 00:15:22.559 align:middle line:84%
Our precious quality
of humanity has

00:15:22.559 --> 00:15:24.600 align:middle line:84%
been turned off, as we'll
see in this next scene.

00:15:24.600 --> 00:15:25.630 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:15:25.630 --> 00:15:31.774 align:middle line:84%
- Our precious quality of
humanity had been turned off.

00:15:31.774 --> 00:15:36.770 align:middle line:84%
But in Emma's tears was the
instruction for an awakening.

00:15:36.770 --> 00:15:39.910 align:middle line:90%
And it spread like wildflowers.

00:15:39.910 --> 00:15:44.860 align:middle line:90%


00:15:44.860 --> 00:15:47.830 align:middle line:84%
People shed their
protective suits.

00:15:47.830 --> 00:15:58.720 align:middle line:90%


00:15:58.720 --> 00:16:04.165 align:middle line:84%
And over time, humanity
blossomed again.

00:16:04.165 --> 00:16:08.620 align:middle line:90%


00:16:08.620 --> 00:16:09.650 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:16:09.650 --> 00:16:11.460 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Well, that really
shows the Adam and Eve

00:16:11.460 --> 00:16:12.030 align:middle line:90%
theme there.

00:16:12.030 --> 00:16:12.830 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Absolutely.

00:16:12.830 --> 00:16:15.330 align:middle line:84%
If we go back to the
great German idealist

00:16:15.330 --> 00:16:17.400 align:middle line:84%
philosopher, Hegel, one
of his important concepts

00:16:17.400 --> 00:16:18.810 align:middle line:90%
is alienation.

00:16:18.810 --> 00:16:20.910 align:middle line:84%
And what we see here
is the alienation

00:16:20.910 --> 00:16:23.430 align:middle line:84%
of not just humans
amongst one another,

00:16:23.430 --> 00:16:25.080 align:middle line:84%
but alienation from
man and nature.

00:16:25.080 --> 00:16:25.880 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Yes.

00:16:25.880 --> 00:16:27.879 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: That was a
fundamental concept for Hegel

00:16:27.879 --> 00:16:31.410 align:middle line:84%
because he felt that modernity
was moving towards alienation,

00:16:31.410 --> 00:16:33.210 align:middle line:90%
principally through technology.

00:16:33.210 --> 00:16:34.800 align:middle line:84%
That technology
would have that force

00:16:34.800 --> 00:16:36.752 align:middle line:90%
of alienating us and nature.

00:16:36.752 --> 00:16:39.210 align:middle line:84%
And I think he's been proven
right about that, whatever one

00:16:39.210 --> 00:16:40.920 align:middle line:90%
thinks of Hegel's philosophy.

00:16:40.920 --> 00:16:43.920 align:middle line:84%
And here, what we're
seeing is humans

00:16:43.920 --> 00:16:47.040 align:middle line:84%
that actually have taken on
non-human characteristics.

00:16:47.040 --> 00:16:48.030 align:middle line:90%
They look like bugs.

00:16:48.030 --> 00:16:49.560 align:middle line:90%
They look alien.

00:16:49.560 --> 00:16:52.510 align:middle line:84%
They're basically wearing
transhumanist exoskeletons

00:16:52.510 --> 00:16:54.910 align:middle line:84%
to even survive in
their environment.

00:16:54.910 --> 00:16:56.760 align:middle line:84%
And as a result,
presumably, they

00:16:56.760 --> 00:17:00.660 align:middle line:84%
can't have natural
intercourse or interrelations.

00:17:00.660 --> 00:17:02.760 align:middle line:84%
And so because of
the restoration

00:17:02.760 --> 00:17:08.849 align:middle line:84%
of the genetic lineage, they're
able to shed these bugs suits.

00:17:08.849 --> 00:17:12.300 align:middle line:84%
And we move back
towards an Edenic state.

00:17:12.300 --> 00:17:14.550 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Yeah, I think
we've been constantly talking

00:17:14.550 --> 00:17:16.740 align:middle line:84%
about these themes
through this series,

00:17:16.740 --> 00:17:19.020 align:middle line:84%
about the natural
state as opposed

00:17:19.020 --> 00:17:21.096 align:middle line:90%
to the transhumanist state.

00:17:21.096 --> 00:17:22.470 align:middle line:84%
And I think a lot
of these movies

00:17:22.470 --> 00:17:24.910 align:middle line:84%
are warning us about
the transhumanism,

00:17:24.910 --> 00:17:29.310 align:middle line:84%
and that going back into nature,
like "Avatar," like the people

00:17:29.310 --> 00:17:31.020 align:middle line:84%
in the future in this
film, where they're

00:17:31.020 --> 00:17:33.420 align:middle line:84%
living in a natural
state, I think

00:17:33.420 --> 00:17:35.370 align:middle line:90%
that's exactly the message.

00:17:35.370 --> 00:17:40.150 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: Yeah, it has an
"X-Men" type message too,

00:17:40.150 --> 00:17:44.010 align:middle line:84%
that there is so much in human
potentiality that the question

00:17:44.010 --> 00:17:45.704 align:middle line:84%
is really, how are
we going to use it?

00:17:45.704 --> 00:17:47.370 align:middle line:84%
It's not whether we
can do these things,

00:17:47.370 --> 00:17:49.710 align:middle line:84%
whether we can develop
these abilities,

00:17:49.710 --> 00:17:51.330 align:middle line:90%
but will it be used wisely?

00:17:51.330 --> 00:17:52.980 align:middle line:84%
And that's really
the key question

00:17:52.980 --> 00:17:55.590 align:middle line:90%
as to how to avert destruction.

00:17:55.590 --> 00:17:56.550 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Yeah.

00:17:56.550 --> 00:17:59.970 align:middle line:84%
Alchemy is really a
combination of science,

00:17:59.970 --> 00:18:01.000 align:middle line:90%
and mythos, and symbol.

00:18:01.000 --> 00:18:01.800 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Right.

00:18:01.800 --> 00:18:04.470 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: And I
think that alchemy

00:18:04.470 --> 00:18:08.460 align:middle line:84%
is, in some ways, the opposite
of the hard tech future,

00:18:08.460 --> 00:18:10.230 align:middle line:84%
even though they both
seem to be heading

00:18:10.230 --> 00:18:11.560 align:middle line:90%
towards the same direction.

00:18:11.560 --> 00:18:14.460 align:middle line:84%
Hard tech is trying
to make us immortal.

00:18:14.460 --> 00:18:16.410 align:middle line:84%
Alchemy promises to
make you immortal.

00:18:16.410 --> 00:18:18.660 align:middle line:84%
And I think in the next film
that we're talking about,

00:18:18.660 --> 00:18:21.750 align:middle line:84%
"9," this really
is a combination

00:18:21.750 --> 00:18:23.295 align:middle line:90%
of alchemy and science.

00:18:23.295 --> 00:18:24.140 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Absolutely.

00:18:24.140 --> 00:18:26.530 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Brilliantly,
I think, presented.

00:18:26.530 --> 00:18:29.790 align:middle line:84%
A very, very much
underrated movie.

00:18:29.790 --> 00:18:32.730 align:middle line:84%
I think "9" is one of the
more interesting movies

00:18:32.730 --> 00:18:34.440 align:middle line:90%
of the early 2000s.

00:18:34.440 --> 00:18:38.070 align:middle line:84%
And so "9" is a
story of another,

00:18:38.070 --> 00:18:41.970 align:middle line:84%
again, dystopian future where
the world has been taken over

00:18:41.970 --> 00:18:43.940 align:middle line:90%
by transhumanism and machines.

00:18:43.940 --> 00:18:44.740 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Right.

00:18:44.740 --> 00:18:47.610 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: An AI has been
invented by a scientist

00:18:47.610 --> 00:18:49.380 align:middle line:90%
and has gotten out of control.

00:18:49.380 --> 00:18:55.550 align:middle line:84%
And he knows that he screwed up,
so he invents nine golem-like

00:18:55.550 --> 00:18:57.990 align:middle line:90%
creatures that he sends--

00:18:57.990 --> 00:19:01.470 align:middle line:84%
that go into the
future after he dies

00:19:01.470 --> 00:19:04.920 align:middle line:84%
to save the world from the
machine intelligence that

00:19:04.920 --> 00:19:06.180 align:middle line:90%
has taken over the world.

00:19:06.180 --> 00:19:07.471 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Yeah, it's interesting.

00:19:07.471 --> 00:19:11.190 align:middle line:84%
This is a very sophisticated
allegory, which we don't often

00:19:11.190 --> 00:19:13.540 align:middle line:90%
see in children's movies.

00:19:13.540 --> 00:19:15.900 align:middle line:84%
It's pretty, most of
the time, on the surface

00:19:15.900 --> 00:19:16.860 align:middle line:90%
what the movie's about.

00:19:16.860 --> 00:19:20.160 align:middle line:84%
Here, it's a very,
