It was meant to be an instrument
of progress, of creation.

00:29:11.310 --> 00:29:16.730 align:middle line:10%
That was the agreement our
chancellor failed to honor.

00:29:16.730 --> 00:29:21.180 align:middle line:10%
Though the fault is
hardly his alone to bear.

00:29:21.180 --> 00:29:27.000 align:middle line:10%
The machine was born purely
of my intellect, which I now

00:29:27.000 --> 00:29:31.590 align:middle line:10%
know was not enough.

00:29:31.590 --> 00:29:36.940 align:middle line:10%
My creation was hopelessly
flawed and indeed dangerous,

00:29:36.940 --> 00:29:42.000 align:middle line:10%
for it lacked the human soul
and could be easily corrupted

00:29:42.000 --> 00:29:44.550 align:middle line:10%
by those who controlled it.

00:29:44.550 --> 00:29:47.390 align:middle line:10%
That is why I am
making each of you.

00:29:47.390 --> 00:29:51.720 align:middle line:10%
You are all that's
left of humanity.

00:29:51.720 --> 00:29:57.002 align:middle line:10%
You are all the
pieces of my soul.

00:29:57.002 --> 00:29:58.710 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: One of the
things that Paracelsus

00:29:58.710 --> 00:30:01.890 align:middle line:84%
talked about in his writings
was the fact that God created us

00:30:01.890 --> 00:30:04.560 align:middle line:84%
out of clay, out of the
matter of the Earth,

00:30:04.560 --> 00:30:08.300 align:middle line:84%
and that without His spirit
being breathed into us,

00:30:08.300 --> 00:30:09.380 align:middle line:90%
we're just husks.

00:30:09.380 --> 00:30:10.180 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Mm-hmm.

00:30:10.180 --> 00:30:11.820 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: And so that's really
the message of this film,

00:30:11.820 --> 00:30:13.920 align:middle line:84%
is that they find their
self, their higher

00:30:13.920 --> 00:30:16.860 align:middle line:84%
self, their true unity, when
they get back to their source.

00:30:16.860 --> 00:30:20.460 align:middle line:84%
And they find where
their origins were,

00:30:20.460 --> 00:30:23.317 align:middle line:84%
and that gives them, then, a
map or a roadway of how to live

00:30:23.317 --> 00:30:25.650 align:middle line:84%
and how to be in the future,
because they've discovered,

00:30:25.650 --> 00:30:26.940 align:middle line:90%
ultimately, freedom.

00:30:26.940 --> 00:30:30.060 align:middle line:84%
And this synthetic determinism
that results from the AI

00:30:30.060 --> 00:30:32.650 align:middle line:90%
is what was impossible.

00:30:32.650 --> 00:30:35.680 align:middle line:84%
It didn't bring what
it promised, the utopia

00:30:35.680 --> 00:30:36.480 align:middle line:90%
that it promised.

00:30:36.480 --> 00:30:40.390 align:middle line:84%
It brought nothing but a
hive-like Borg existence.

00:30:40.390 --> 00:30:42.600 align:middle line:84%
And so they finally free
themselves from this

00:30:42.600 --> 00:30:43.680 align:middle line:90%
and find their soul.

00:30:43.680 --> 00:30:45.660 align:middle line:84%
And I think that that's
a perennial message

00:30:45.660 --> 00:30:47.010 align:middle line:90%
that we can all take away.

00:30:47.010 --> 00:30:49.320 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Yeah, it was
a really good ending.

00:30:49.320 --> 00:30:53.490 align:middle line:84%
The matrix that Paracelsus
is talking about

00:30:53.490 --> 00:30:56.610 align:middle line:90%
is associated with that clay.

00:30:56.610 --> 00:31:00.900 align:middle line:84%
In other words, when he's
talking about that matrix,

00:31:00.900 --> 00:31:03.870 align:middle line:84%
he's saying that the
matrix is both part of us

00:31:03.870 --> 00:31:05.400 align:middle line:90%
and separate from us.

00:31:05.400 --> 00:31:07.980 align:middle line:84%
And that we can use
that matrix to perform

00:31:07.980 --> 00:31:09.450 align:middle line:90%
our alchemical experiments.

00:31:09.450 --> 00:31:10.250 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Mm-hmm.

00:31:10.250 --> 00:31:12.780 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: And truly,
the matrix is the clay.

00:31:12.780 --> 00:31:14.400 align:middle line:84%
It's the stuff that
makes this world.

00:31:14.400 --> 00:31:16.858 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: It's the prima materia
that Aristotle talked about,

00:31:16.858 --> 00:31:18.780 align:middle line:84%
which is that
first-formed matter.

00:31:18.780 --> 00:31:21.030 align:middle line:84%
And then God the
Creator then forms it

00:31:21.030 --> 00:31:24.090 align:middle line:90%
into some being or some object.

00:31:24.090 --> 00:31:26.460 align:middle line:84%
But it's still not anything
without the breath of life

00:31:26.460 --> 00:31:27.390 align:middle line:90%
that comes from Him.

00:31:27.390 --> 00:31:27.840 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: That's right.

00:31:27.840 --> 00:31:29.820 align:middle line:84%
And at the end, the
creatures are finally

00:31:29.820 --> 00:31:33.570 align:middle line:84%
imbued with the creative
soul, and they ascend up

00:31:33.570 --> 00:31:34.650 align:middle line:90%
into the stars.

00:31:34.650 --> 00:31:35.450 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Exactly.

00:31:35.450 --> 00:31:38.640 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: At once, this is a
grim movie, but also a hopeful

00:31:38.640 --> 00:31:39.450 align:middle line:90%
film.

00:31:39.450 --> 00:31:41.910 align:middle line:84%
And the thing I like
best about this movie,

00:31:41.910 --> 00:31:44.250 align:middle line:84%
besides the
interesting plot twist,

00:31:44.250 --> 00:31:46.650 align:middle line:84%
is the architecture
of the film itself--

00:31:46.650 --> 00:31:50.760 align:middle line:84%
the cathedrals, the
cities, the room

00:31:50.760 --> 00:31:52.450 align:middle line:90%
where the scientist lives in.

00:31:52.450 --> 00:31:55.620 align:middle line:84%
It's all filled with
amazing amounts of detail

00:31:55.620 --> 00:31:58.060 align:middle line:84%
that the filmmakers just did
a great job of putting in.

00:31:58.060 --> 00:31:58.860 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Yeah.

00:31:58.860 --> 00:32:01.440 align:middle line:10%
Once they discover their
source, once they discover

00:32:01.440 --> 00:32:04.101 align:middle line:10%
the principle of life,
as you mentioned,

00:32:04.101 --> 00:32:05.100 align:middle line:10%
they ascended to heaven.

00:32:05.100 --> 00:32:07.710 align:middle line:10%
And we see this
scene where it rains.

00:32:07.710 --> 00:32:11.220 align:middle line:10%
So presumably, the spirits that
have ascended, it sends a rain,

00:32:11.220 --> 00:32:13.480 align:middle line:10%
and we see vegetation
spring back.

00:32:13.480 --> 00:32:15.022 align:middle line:10%
So the principle
of life, actually,

00:32:15.022 --> 00:32:17.480 align:middle line:10%
finally comes back, which has
been missing this whole time.

00:32:17.480 --> 00:32:19.069 align:middle line:10%
And I think that's
a great message.

00:32:19.069 --> 00:32:20.110 align:middle line:10%
>>WEIDNER: That is right.

00:32:20.110 --> 00:32:20.985 align:middle line:10%
That's exactly right.

00:32:20.985 --> 00:32:22.750 align:middle line:10%
That's what happened
in King Arthur.

00:32:22.750 --> 00:32:26.100 align:middle line:10%
When he's rejuvenated,
the rains come back,

00:32:26.100 --> 00:32:27.780 align:middle line:10%
and the kingdom grows.

00:32:27.780 --> 00:32:29.070 align:middle line:10%
And that's what happens here.

00:32:29.070 --> 00:32:32.040 align:middle line:10%
That is the ultimate alchemy,
is to take the darkness

00:32:32.040 --> 00:32:34.900 align:middle line:10%
and turn it into light,
to turn it into life.

00:32:34.900 --> 00:32:36.900 align:middle line:84%
And that's what happens
at the end of this film.

00:32:36.900 --> 00:32:40.590 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: My takeaway from this
is that we have two children's

00:32:40.590 --> 00:32:44.640 align:middle line:84%
films that tell us
vast allegorical truths

00:32:44.640 --> 00:32:48.270 align:middle line:84%
about the history, origins,
and the destiny of man.

00:32:48.270 --> 00:32:51.120 align:middle line:84%
They function as a
warning about tech.

00:32:51.120 --> 00:32:53.130 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
ultimately, what we

00:32:53.130 --> 00:32:55.260 align:middle line:84%
see is the secret
to our existence

00:32:55.260 --> 00:32:58.230 align:middle line:84%
can be found in our
origin, in our creator.

00:32:58.230 --> 00:33:00.480 align:middle line:84%
And then that will
also give us a map

00:33:00.480 --> 00:33:03.012 align:middle line:84%
to avoid the many,
many cycles in the past

00:33:03.012 --> 00:33:04.470 align:middle line:84%
that we've seen
throughout history.

00:33:04.470 --> 00:33:06.570 align:middle line:84%
Oswald Spengler
talked about history

00:33:06.570 --> 00:33:10.390 align:middle line:84%
as a constant cycle
of man's failures.

00:33:10.390 --> 00:33:13.050 align:middle line:84%
And I think that if we
can learn from history,

00:33:13.050 --> 00:33:15.270 align:middle line:84%
as Santayana said,
the philosopher,

00:33:15.270 --> 00:33:17.910 align:middle line:84%
if we can learn from history,
we can avoid those mistakes,

00:33:17.910 --> 00:33:19.470 align:middle line:90%
and we can have a bright future.

00:33:19.470 --> 00:33:20.470 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: That's right.

00:33:20.470 --> 00:33:22.350 align:middle line:84%
I think it was HG
Wells who said,

00:33:22.350 --> 00:33:25.560 align:middle line:84%
"History is a race between
education and disaster."

00:33:25.560 --> 00:33:28.360 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's what
these movies are also about,

00:33:28.360 --> 00:33:30.570 align:middle line:84%
is trying to educate
us as to what

00:33:30.570 --> 00:33:34.620 align:middle line:84%
these potential disasters in
the dystopian future will be

00:33:34.620 --> 00:33:36.109 align:middle line:90%
and how to avoid them.

00:33:36.109 --> 00:33:38.400 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: Join us again next
time on "Hollywood Decoded."

00:33:38.400 --> 00:33:39.210 align:middle line:90%
I'm Jay Dyer.

00:33:39.210 --> 00:33:40.501 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: And I'm Jay Weidner.

00:33:40.501 --> 00:33:41.730 align:middle line:90%
Thanks for watching.

